# Alaya Domain Hard Lessons

Compressed from Claude project memory and recall waves. Do not re-learn by
reverting these. Algorithm details live in `.do-it/findings` / handbook — this
is the behavioral guardrail.

## Ranking vs coverage

- Recall is two problems: (1) relevance ranking, (2) answer-set coverage.
  Coverage/path/session signals in point-wise ranking often destroy ranking;
  put set-coverage in delivery, not as a ranking replace.
- Prefer additive RRF (or flat additive) as the ranking base; use axes as
  bounded refinement on top (compose, do not replace). Saturating noisy-OR /
  multiplicative collapses that bury embedding rescue have already failed
  catastrophically in bench — do not revive without new independent proof.
- Structural/topology "reserve" injection and correlated lexical double-count
  can look like gains while injecting noise — measure both any@5 and
  full-gold / single-fact, not one KPI.

## Measurement honesty

- R@5 any-gold alone is a trap; full-gold / coverage is often the real wall.
- Embedding-ON claims need proof the embedding path is actually live (silent
  OFF has happened). Cosine is within-model only — do not treat raw cosine as
  a cross-model magnitude.
- Judge/answer model choice can deflate preference scores; blame recall only
  after ruling out judge/harness artifacts.
- Single-card A/B is a probe, not a death sentence — think read/write/recall
  as one pipeline. Neutral results can expose the next seam.
- Benchmark scope is exact: if the user says recall-only / no chat / no QA,
  keep that boundary. Defer benches until explicitly reopened. Align cache
  manifest, extraction model, and prompt hash before launch.

## Product / i18n / hygiene

- Multilingual from the start: CJK must segment in tokenizers and lexical
  overlap metrics — English whitespace tokenizers silently break HQ/facet.
- Do not re-propose already-landed-and-neutral levers (anchor lane, workspace
  activation weight, claim-key write-side for preference) without new evidence.
- Prefer worktree isolation for parallel waves; archive superseded `.do-it`
  plan/findings layers before pointing runtime at a new card.
